title: Documentary Review Episode 1 - Khrushchev Does America
itunes:author: The History of the Cold War Podcast
itunes:summary:
Jeff and Dave review the 2013 Documentary Khrushchev Does America by Tim Toidze.  

Per IMBD: 

     The  story of the unconditional, no-holds-barred tour of America by Soviet  Premier Nikita Khrushchev, leader of World Communism and America's arch  nemesis, during 13 sun-filled days in the fall of 1959.

For pictures for this episode and more go to our website at:  www.historyofthecoldwarpodcast.com/
